⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Conch
node LMZ · LMZ · ⟦The Conch:LMZ:b78378⟧

WHO   — The Conch — commands the spiders
WHAT  — The strangest gift: control of living things by tone, the toy that turns a boy into something the natural world obeys.
WHERE — LMZ · The Last Mimzy (2007)  Framework inputs: The Last Mimzy (2007, dir. Robert Shaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's wonder includes dominion over the small and many, and the conch is its voice.
HOW   — By translating sound into command, so that the spiders move to Noah's will.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Blow through me and the spiders listen. I am how a boy learned that even the smallest living things would answer a kind, strange call.

